		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If the system can perform frequency sweeps and hardware volume envelopes, then it has to have the APU frame counter.  Whether or not it will generate interrupts is a different question.
<br />
<br />Dragon Warrior (US version) doesn't use Frame IRQs.  It's Dragon Quest (Japanese version) that does.  Same for Dragon Quest 2.
<br />
<br />I have no idea why Dragon Warrior 1 would fail on a famiclone.  It works so well on every emulator in existence.  Some kind of electrical or hardware incompatibility?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


