		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think I got my answer from watching the Battletoads video.  Sound sweeps go higher than normal, so it's clocking the frame counter at normal NTSC clock cycle counts.</div>
<br />Not quite. NTSC Famcom CPU core runs at 21.47727/12=1,7897725MHz. Dendy CPU core runs at 26.601712/15=1,77344746MHz. Difference is more than 0,9%.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
